# Cursor AI — Project Rules

Follow the workflow, commit standards, testing, and implementation rules defined in [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md).
This file contains Cursor-specific guidance only.

---

## Ticket Selection

- Auto-fetch the top In-Progress ticket from the project board.
  Column name may vary (e.g., "In-Progress", "In Progress"); match flexibly.
- If no in-progress ticket exists, prompt the user for a new ticket idea.

## Branch Base

- Before starting the next ticket after a merge, switch back to `main` and update it from `origin`.
- Create the new `feature/[ticket-id]-[description]` branch from that refreshed `main`.
- Do not branch from the previous feature branch or from a stale local `main`.

## Dependency Sync

After creating or switching to a branch, sync deps in `web/`:
- If `pnpm-lock.yaml` exists → `pnpm install`
- Else if `yarn.lock` → `yarn install --frozen-lockfile`
- Else if `package-lock.json` → `npm ci` (fallback: `npm install`)

## MCP Guidance

- Use the GitHub MCP server to query the project board, create issues, labels, and comments.
- Use the Playwright MCP server (when available) to run headless verifications.
- Project board: https://github.com/users/tonym999/projects/2

## Code Review Triage (CodeRabbit)

After a PR review, use the GitHub MCP or `gh` CLI to fetch and process feedback:

```
gh api --paginate repos/tonym999/patofalltrades/pulls/{PR_NUMBER}/reviews
gh api --paginate repos/tonym999/patofalltrades/pulls/{PR_NUMBER}/comments
gh api --paginate repos/tonym999/patofalltrades/issues/{PR_NUMBER}/comments
gh api graphql -f query='query { repository(owner: "tonym999", name: "patofalltrades") { pullRequest(number: {PR_NUMBER}) { reviewThreads(first: 100) { nodes { id isResolved path line comments(first: 20) { nodes { id databaseId body author { login } createdAt url } } } } } } }'
```

- Filter to comments authored by `coderabbitai[bot]`.
- Use GraphQL `reviewThreads` or GitHub MCP to determine unresolved vs resolved threads; the REST endpoints do not expose `isResolved`.
- Follow the triage flow in [AGENTS.md — Code Review Handling](AGENTS.md#code-review-handling).
- Present unresolved threads to the user grouped by priority (change requests → nitpicks → informational).
- After fixes are pushed, resolve addressed threads via the API or prompt the user to resolve them on GitHub.

## AI Skills

Check `.cursor/skills/` for domain-specific guidance:
- `frontend-ui` — building/refactoring UI components
- `accessibility-audit` — auditing and improving accessibility
- `design-review` — reviewing visual hierarchy, spacing, polish

## Definition of Done (per ticket)

- Branch created following the naming pattern
- Implementation complete and lint-clean
- Playwright smoke test present
- Commit(s) use conventional commits
- Branch pushed and PR created
- Issue and PR on the project board in the correct column
